# API layer (Presentation)

## Read first

- `internal/api/router.go` — route table
- `internal/infrastructure/temporal/order_service.go` — workflow start/update/query
- [docs/design_overview.md](../../docs/design_overview.md) §4

## Boundaries

- Handlers call `OrderService` (Temporal client); they do **not** mutate seat inventory directly.
- **Exception:** `GET /api/v1/flights/{flight_id}/seats` reads `SeatRepository` directly (read path only).
- Do **not** call `TryHold`, `Release`, `Confirm`, or `SwapHold` from handlers.
- DTOs live in `internal/api/dto/`; map domain/workflow types at the handler edge.
- Payment code format validation may exist in handlers for HTTP 400; business rules (3×3, timer) belong in the workflow.

## Tests

- Handler unit tests: `internal/api/handler/*_test.go`
- End-to-end HTTP: `internal/api/order_integration_test.go`, `integration_test.go`
